  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CTDO_Crisis Modifier III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection of the fragile resilience gains that vulnerable individuals, households and communities in category B1 and B2 have made over the past year and beyond</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Crisis Modifier provides a practical means to avert or reduce the impact of threats and shocks namely; low crop harvest, crop pests and diseases, livestock diseases, water shortages  and water borne diseases. as a result of a poor rainfall season, the project will protect beneficiaries&#x2019; production and productivity whilst protecting resilience gains made by communities as a result of ZRBF BRACT and other efforts. The project provides market based input support to increase production of drought tolerant crops, rehabilitate community irrigation schemes and water harvesting infrastructure to improve and diversify crop production as well improve access to food, feed and water.</narrative>
  </description>
